  "body": "**What would you like to be added**:\r\nA way to set generic flags when calling the conformance test image.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nCurrently it just respects a handful of flags in an effort to be simple for callers. However, someone has reported a need to set one of the DNS flags https://github.com/heptio/sonobuoy/issues/733 and there isn't a real reason we don't surface _that_ flag. The problem is that there are so many other options, we'd have to add N env vars and keep it up to date as new flags get added.\r\n\r\nInstead I think it might make sense to just add 2 more env vars: `GINKGO_FLAGS` and `E2E_FLAGS` which would all the user to set arbitrary values. Consider the previous env vars as easy-buttons and these as power-user functions. If set, we'd just append those to the ginkgo/e2e flags we invoke the tests with.\r\n\r\nThis would unblock any testing need related to flags.\r\n\r\n/sig testing\r\n/area conformance",
